# provider-caps — kit-owned per-provider capability facts (ADR 011).
#
# The single source for the facts that decide which providers land in each
# derived wiring set. An adopter declares ONE list in harness.conf —
# HARNESS_PROVIDERS (the provider dirs this repo wires) — and the kit derives
# the per-facet sets (skill stubs, agent stubs, hook wiring) by filtering that
# list through the capability columns below. Correct membership is kit
# knowledge (does .codex read .agents/ natively? does .opencode have a bash
# hook shim?), not repo policy, so it lives here, in exactly one place.
#
# This file is MECHANISM: integrity-pinned in scripts/harness/.harness-manifest
# and guard-config-protected, like kit-manifest — it is read by check-harness
# and sync to derive validated wiring sets. Plain text, bash-3.2
# read/awk-parseable, no jq (ADR 002). '#' lines and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Columns (whitespace-separated):
#   1 provider       provider dir (leading '.', e.g. .claude). NOT .agents —
#                    .agents/skills/ is the canonical home, never a wiring
#                    target, so it has no row.
#   2 skill_stubs    yes|no. 'no' ⇔ the provider reads .agents/skills/
#                    natively (Codex) and is excluded from generated skill stubs.
#   3 agent_dialect  md | toml | md-subagent | none. How the generated agent
#                    stub renders (Codex = TOML; OpenCode = Markdown + a
#                    `mode: subagent` line); 'none' = receives no agent stub.
#   4 hook_config    <path>:<shape> | none. The provider's hook-wiring config
#                    and its jq shape (nested|flat); 'none' = no bash hook shim
#                    (OpenCode is descoped, per the frozen provider matrix).
#   5 exec_config    <path>:<checker> | none. The provider's execution-profile
#                    config and the check-harness #8e validator that reads it.
#
# Adding a provider is a one-row change here plus its frozen hook-tuple table
# and #8e validator in check-instructions.sh (the event/matcher contract and
# the security-floor keys are richer than a table cell).
#
# provider   skill_stubs  agent_dialect  hook_config                    exec_config
.claude      yes          md             .claude/settings.json:nested   .claude/settings.json:claude
.cursor      yes          md             .cursor/hooks.json:flat        .cursor/sandbox.json:cursor
.codex       no           toml           .codex/hooks.json:nested       .codex/config.toml:codex
.opencode    yes          md-subagent    none                           opencode.json:opencode
